name: cellulitis
definition: Cellulitis is a musculoskeletal system symptom characterized as a diffuse and especially subcutaneous inflammation of connective tissue.

name: ataxia
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by an inability to coordinate voluntary muscular movements that is symptomatic of some nervous disorders.

name: backache
definition: A pain that is characterized by occurring in the lower back.

name: bleeding
definition: A general symptom that is characterized as an act, instance, or result of being bled or the process by which something is bled: as a the escape of blood from vessels.

name: blister
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a fluid-filled elevation of the epidermis.

name: blurred vision
definition: A vision symptom that is characterized by a decreased clarity or sharpness in vision, which can be caused by eye conditions myopia or hyperopia.

name: confusion
definition: A balance symptom that is characterized by a disturbance of consciousness characterized by inability to engage in orderly thought or by lack of power to distinguish, choose, or act decisively.

name: dehydration
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by an abnormal depletion of body fluids.

name: delirium
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a mental disturbance characterized by confusion, disordered speech, and hallucinations.

name: depression
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a chronic feeling of emptiness, sadness, or inability to feel pleasure that may appear to happen for no clear reason.  Additionally one may experience feelings of hopelessness, pessimism, irritability, frustration, or restlessness, guilt, worthlessness and thoughts of death or suicide.

name: disorientation
definition: A confusion that is characterized by an usually transient state of confusion especially as to time, place, or identity; often as a result of disease or drugs.

name: drowsiness
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a feeling of being more sleepy than normal during the day. People who are drowsy may fall asleep in when they do not want to or at times which can lead to safety concerns.

name: dry cough
definition: A cough that is characterized by a lack of accompanied phlegm production.

name: paralysis
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by a complete or partial loss of function especially when involving the power of motion or of sensation in any part of the body.

name: dyspneic enteritis
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by being short or breath or out of air (dyspnea), with inflammation of the small intestine (enteritis).

name: enteritis
definition: Enteritis is a digestive system symptom involving the inflammation of the small intestines and especially of the human ileum.

name: hematuria
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the presence of blood or blood cells in the urine.

name: hemorrhage
definition: A cardiovascular system symptom that is characterized by an acute loss of blood from a damaged blood vessel.

name: obsolete hyperkeratotic plaques of surface of foot
hyperpigmentation
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an excess pigmentation in a bodily part or tissue, as the skin.

name: inflammation
definition: Inflammation is a general symptom where there is a local response to cellular injury that is marked by capillary dilatation, leukocytic infiltration, redness, heat, pain, swelling, and often loss of function and that serves as a mechanism initiating the elimination of noxious agents and of damaged tissue.

name: joint pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in or around a joint.

name: lethargy
definition: A fatigue that is characterized by abnormal drowsiness.

name: coordination symptom
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by the harmonious functioning of interrelated organs and body parts; in particular the working together of muscle groups in the execution of complicated movements.

name: meningoencephalitis
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of the brain and meninges.

name: encephalitis
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by inflammation of the brain tissue, which is typically caused by a viral infection, but it may also be caused by bacterial or parasitic infections, cancer, or certain drugs or toxins.

name: mild encephalitis
definition: An encephalitis that is not intense (not severe).

name: skin lesion
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an abnormal change in structure of the skin that is especially circumscribed and well defined due to injury or disease.

name: nephritis
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the acute or chronic inflammation of the kidney affecting the structure (as of the glomerulus or parenchyma) and caused by infection, a degenerative process, or vascular disease.

name: pain
definition: A sensation perception that is characterized by an unpleasant sensation that usually indicates the body is threatened or damaged. The sensation may be sharp or dull, short-lived or chronic, intermittent or continual, confined to one area or spread over the entire body.

name: peritonitis
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of the peritoneum.

name: pleural effusion
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an exudation of fluid from the blood or lymph into a pleural cavity.

name: prostration
definition: Prostration is a general symptom characterized by complete physical or mental exhaustion.

name: rales
definition: An abnormal chest sound that is characterized by the clicking, rattling, or crackling noises heard on auscultation of (listening to) the lung with a stethoscope during inhalation. The sounds are caused by the 'popping open' of small airways and alveoli collapsed by fluid, exudate, or lack of aeration during expiration. The word 'rales' derives from the French word rale meaning 'rattle'. Rales can be heard in patients with pneumonia, atelectasis, pulmonary fibrosis, acute bronchitis, or bronchiectasis. Pulmonary edema secondary to left-sided congestive heart failure can also cause rales.

name: severe joint pain
definition: A joint pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in or around a joint that is intense (severe).

name: necrosis
definition: Necrosis is a general symptom where death of a portion of tissue differentially affected by local injury (as loss of blood supply, corrosion, burning, or the local lesion of a disease).

name: skin ulcer
definition: A skin lesion that is characterized by a break in skin with loss of surface tissue, disintegration and necrosis of epithelial tissue, and often pus.

name: sneezing
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a sudden violent spasmodic audible expiration of breath through the nose and mouth especially as a reflex act following irritation of the nasal mucous membrane.

name: spasticity
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by an abnormal increase in muscle tone or stiffness of muscle, which might interfere with movement, speech, or be associated with discomfort or pain.

name: obsolete bronchopneumonia
definition: A pneumonia that is characterized by acute inflammation of the bronchi, accompanied by inflamed patches in the nearby lobules of the lungs

name: obsolete sudden onset of severe chills
thirst
definition: Thirst is a general symptom characterized by a sensation of dryness in the mouth and throat associated with a desire for liquids.

name: tremor
definition: Tremor is a generial symptom characterized by a trembling or shaking usually from physical weakness, emotional stress, or disease.

name: incoordination
definition: A coordination symptom that is characterized by a loss of complicated body movements, which may be caused by disease, injury, or toxins.

name: obsolete vesicular lesions on lip border
wasting
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by the unintended loss of weight and lean body tissue characteristic of many diseases (as cancer, tuberculosis, and AIDS).

name: weight loss
definition: A weight symptom that is characterized by a reduction of the total body mass, by a mean loss of fluid, body fat (adipose tissue), or lean mass (namely bone mineral deposits, muscle, tendon, and other connective tissue). Weight loss can either occur unintentionally because of malnourishment or an underlying disease.

name: weariness
definition: A fatigue that is characterized by a feeling of exhaustion in strength, endurance, and vigor.

name: exhaustion
definition: A fatigue that is characterized by a feeling of weariness (bodily or mental) or feeling of weakness.  Exhaustion is a shorter-lived form of fatigue that can be experienced emotionally, mentally, and physically.

name: tiredness
definition: A fatigue that is characterized by a feeling of a lessened capacity for work and reduced efficiency of accomplishment, usually accompanied by a sense of weariness and fatigue.

name: abortion
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by the expulsion of a fetus at any time before completion of pregnancy and is often due to infection.

name: miscarriage
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by the spontaneous expulsion of a human fetus before it is viable and especially between the 12th and 28th weeks of gestation.

name: spontaneous abortion
definition: An abortion that is characterized by the natural occurring expulsion of a nonviable fetus.

name: acute meningoencephalitis
definition: A meningoencephalitis that is characterized by a severe and sudden onset.

name: afebrile
definition: A fever that is characterized by the state of being free from fever.

name: agraphia
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by a pathological loss of the ability to write.

name: anomia
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by a severe problem with recalling words or names.

name: inability to comprehend speech
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by a loss of ability to comprehend speech.

name: inability to speak
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by a loss of ability to speak.

name: inability to form words
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by a loss of ability to form words.

name: poor enunciation
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by a loss of ability to properly enunciate words.

name: receptive aphasia
definition: An inability to comprehend speech that is characterized by an inability to understand spoken, written, or tactile speech symbols that results from damage (as by a brain lesion) to an area of the brain (as Wernicke's area) concerned with language.

name: atrial fibrillation
definition: A cardiac fibrillation consisting of a very rapid uncoordinated contractions of the atria of the heart resulting in a lack of synchronism between heartbeat and pulse beat.

name: bradycardia
definition: Bradycardia is a cardiovascular system symptom consisting of a relatively slow heart action whether physiological or pathological.

name: bronchiolitis
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of the bronchioles.

name: colic
definition: A pain that is characterized by the condition marked by recurrent episodes of prolonged and uncontrollable crying and irritability in an otherwise healthy infant that is of unknown cause and usually subsides after three to four months of age.

name: colicky pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by an attack of acute abdominal pain localized in a hollow organ or part (as the small intestine, ureter, or bile duct) and often caused by spasm, obstruction, or twisting.

name: congestion
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an excessive accumulation especially of blood or mucus.

name: cough with bloody sputum
definition: A cough that is characterized by production and expectoration (bringing up) of sputum that is bright red or pink and frothy.

name: cyclic fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by occurring during periodic episodes.

name: decreased appetite
definition: An alteration of appetite that is characterized by a reduced desire to eat.

name: increased appetite
definition: An alteration of appetite that is characterized by an desire to eat, an excess desire for food.

name: proprioception symptom
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by one's body’s ability to sense movement, action, and location and results from sensory receptors in one's nervous system and body (muscles, joints, and tendons).

name: decreased conscious proprioception
definition: A proprioception symptom that is characterized by a decreased ability of an organism to consciously process the reception of stimuli produced within the organism.

name: dermal abscess
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a pus-filled pocket in the skin, similar to a pimple, but larger and deeper.  The pocket is filled with bacteria, white blood cells, and dead skin and typcally result from the bacteria Staphylococcus aureus prentrating the skin through a cut or hair follicle.

name: diffuse rash
definition: A rash characterized by large patches of red skin, without overlying changes in the epidermis.

name: dry hacking cough
definition: A dry cough that is characterized by a rough and loud sound.

name: epididymitis
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of the epididymis.

name: epididymorchitis
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by inflammation of the epididymis and/or testicle (testis).

name: extreme exhaustion
definition: An exhaustion that is characterized by exceeding the ordinary, usual, or expected.

name: extreme fatigue
definition: A fatigue that is characterized by exceeding the ordinary, usual, or expected.

name: flaccid paralysis
definition: A paralysis that is charicterized by a lack of muscle tone in the affected muscles and in which tendon reflexes are decreased or absent.

name: arrhythmia
definition: Arrhythmia is a cardiovascular system symptom consisting of an alteration in rhythm of the heartbeat either in time or force.

name: eczema
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an inflammatory condition of the skin with redness, itching, and oozing vesicular lesions, which become scaly, crusted, or hardened.

name: belching
definition: Belching is a digestive system symptom involving the sudden expulsion of gas from the stomach through the mouth.

name: hemiparesis
definition: A paralysis that is characterized by a weakness or the inability to move on one side of the body.

name: hepatic abscess
definition: hepatic abscess is a liver symptom characterized by a pus-filled mass in the liver that can develop from injury to the liver or an intraabdominal infection disseminated from the portal circulation.

name: hyperemia
definition: Hyperemia is a hemic system symptom consisting of an excess of blood in a body part as from an increased flow of blood due to vasodilation.

name: hyperesthesia
definition: A sensation perception that is characterized by an increased sensitivity to stimulation.

name: hypothermia
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a subnormal temperature of the body, as defined by a temperature under 36.6 degrees Celcius (97.8 degrees Fahrenheit).

name: impaired coordination
definition: A coordination symptom that is characterized by weakened or imperfect body complicated  movement, which may be caused by disease, injury, or toxins.

name: inability to feed
definition: A feeding difficulties and mismanagement that is characterized by a lack of feeding capacity.

name: loss of appetite
definition: An alteration of appetite that is characterized by a loss of desire to eat, i.e. no desire to eat.

name: keratitis
exact_synonym: inflammation of the cornea of the eye

name: loss of balance
definition: A  balance symptom that is characterized by an inability to stay upright and move confidently.  Loss of balance may be due to problems in the inner ear, the brain, or the heart. Aging, infections, head injury, certain medicines, and problems with blood circulation may also cause balance problems.

name: low birth weight
definition: A weight symptom that is characterized by an infant weighing 5.5 pounds (2500 grams) or less at birth.  Low birth weight may occur with premature birth, or due to smoking cigarettes, secondhand tobacco smoke exposure, drinking alcohol, and taking certain drugs during pregnancy.

name: melena
definition: A feces and droppings symptom that is characterized by the passage of dark tarry stools containing decomposing blood that is usually an indication of bleeding in the upper part of the alimentary canal and especially the esophagus, stomach, and duodenum.

name: bronchitis
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an acute or chronic inflammation of the bronchial tubes.

name: tetanic convulsion
definition: A convulsion that is characterized by a tonic spasm (prolonged contraction of the muscles), without loss of consciousness and often associated with hypocalcemia.

name: mild tetanic convulsion
definition: A tetanic convulsion that is not intense (not severe).

name: muscle ache
definition: A pain that is characterized by a continuous or prolonged dull pain.

name: limb edema
definition: An adema that is characterized by an abnormal excess accumulation of serous fluid in connective tissue of the limbs.

name: painful lymph glands
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in the lymph gland (lymph node). Pain is often associated with swelling of the gland, which is a sign that one's body is fighting an infection.

name: palpebral edema
definition: An adema that is characterized by an abnormal excess accumulation of serous fluid in connective tissue of the eyelids.

name: panting respiration
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by short, shallow, and rapid breathing.

name: papule
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a small solid usually conical elevation of the skin caused by inflammation, accumulated secretion, or hypertrophy of tissue elements.

name: paraplegia
definition: A paralysis that is characterized by a complete, or partial, loss of function of the lower half of the body with involvement of both legs that is usually due to injury or disease of the spinal cord in the thoracic or lumbar region.

name: obsolete partial paralysis of the limbs
phlegm
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a viscid mucus secreted in abnormal quantity in the respiratory passages.

name: pneumonitis
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of lung tissue. Pneumonia is one type of pneumonitis caused by an infection. Many other factors can cause pneumonitis, including breathing in animal dander, inhaling small food particles 'down the wrong pipe' and receiving radiation therapy to your chest.

name: poor feeding
definition: A feeding difficulties and mismanagement that is characterized by an infant with little interest in feeding and it can also refer to an infant who is not feeding enough to receive the necessary nutrition required for adequate growth.

name: premature labor
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by labor occurring before 37 full weeks of pregnancy.

name: emaciation
definition: A wasting that is characterized by the state of being extremely thin as a result of an absence of body fat and very week as a result of muscle wasting; usually because of illness or extreme hunger.

name: progressive emaciation
definition: An emaciation that is characterized by an increase in scope or severity with time.

name: prostatic abscess
definition: A prostate symptom that is characterized by a localized collection of purulent fluid within the prostate, often forming as a complication of acute bacterial prostatitis.

name: prostatic infection
definition: A prostate symptom that is characterized by inflammation of the prostate and surrounding area.

name: proteinuria
definition: A urinary system symptom characterized by the presence of excess protein in the urine.

name: proximal paralysis of arm and leg
ptosis
definition: Ptosis is a general symptom characterized by a sagging or prolapse of an organ or part.

name: renal abscess
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by a pocket (a walled-off cavity) of pus that develops in the kidney tissue. It results from the migration of bacteria from another infection site on the body to the kidneys.

name: respiratory paralysis
definition: A paralysis that is characterized by a complete or severe weakness of the muscles of respiration.

name: rhinorrhea
definition: A nose symptom that is characterized by an excessive secretion of mucous through the nose.

name: scrotal abscess
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by an abscess that is either superficial or intrascrotal.  Superficial scrotal abscess may occur from an infected hair follicle, infection of a scrotal laceration, or minor scrotal surgery.  Intrascrotal abscess most commonly arises from bacterial epididymitis, but may also be related to tuberculous infection of the epididymis, a testicular abscess that ruptures through the tunica albuginea, or drainage of appendicitis into scrotum through a patent processus vaginalis or as a result of extravasation of infected urine from the urethra in patients with a urethral stricture and neurogenic bladder using an external collection device.

name: obsolete mastitis
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of the mammary gland or udder and usually caused by infection.

name: obsolete severe mastitis
definition: A mastitis that is characterized by an increased intensity or severity of the condition.

name: severe myalgia
definition: A muscle pain that is characterized by being severe in nature.  Myalgia may be acute in nature, stemming from overuse of a muscle group or viral infection.  It may also be chronic and caused by  metabolic myopathy, some nutritional deficiencies, and chronic fatigue syndrome.

name: stupor
definition: An alteration of consciousness that is characterized by a lack of critical mental function and a level of consciousness, in which an affected person is almost entirely unresponsive and responds only to intense stimuli such as pain.

name: vaginal discharge
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by fluid made by glands inside the vagina and cervix carrying away dead cells and bacteria. While it is normal for odor and color to vary, vaginal itching or burning may be indicative of an infection.

name: vertigo
definition: A dizziness that is characterized by a specific type of dizziness, a major symptom of a balance disorder. It is the sensation of spinning or swaying while the body is stationary with respect to the surroundings.

name: cachexia
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by a general physical wasting and malnutrition usually associated with chronic disease.

name: weight gain
definition: A weight symptom that is characterized by an increase in body weight. This can involve an increase in muscle mass, fat deposits, excess fluids such as water or other factors.

name: vaginismus
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by a painful spasmodic contraction of the vagina.

name: bruise
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an injury transmitted through unbroken skin to underlying tissue causing rupture of small blood vessels and escape of blood into the tissue with resulting discoloration.

name: syncope
definition: An alteration of consciousness that is characterized by a loss of consciousness resulting from insufficient blood flow to the brain.

name: cataplexy
definition: Cataplexy is a muscle symptom characterized by a sudden loss of muscle control with retention of clear consciousness that follows a strong emotional stimulus (as elation, surprise, or anger) and is a characteristic symptom of narcolepsy.

name: hyperthermia
definition: A high fever that is characterized by an exceptionally high fever especially when induced artificially for therapeutic purposes.

name: anxiety
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a painful or apprehensive uneasiness of mind usually over an impending or anticipated ill.

name: catatonia
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a marked psychomotor disturbance that may involve stupor or mutism, negativism, rigidity, purposeless excitement, echolalia, echopraxia, and inappropriate or bizarre posturing and is associated with various medical conditions (as schizophrenia and mood disorders).

name: dysarthria
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a difficulty in articulating words due to disease of the central nervous system.

name: bloating
definition: Bloating is a digestive system symptom involving the accumulation of gas in the digestive tract and resulting in abdominal distension.

name: hematochezia
definition: hematochezia is a feces and droppings symptom characterized by the passage of fresh blood per anus, usually in or with stools.

name: dyspepsia
definition: Dyspepsia is a digestive system symptom referred to as indigestion resulting from an impairment to digestion caused by ulcer, gall bladder disease or inflamed colon. Related symptoms include weakness, loss of appetite, and depression.

name: pyrosis
definition: From synonym: Heartburn is a pain characterized by a painful burning feeling in your chest or throat that happens when stomach acid backs up into your esophagus.

name: claudication
definition: A pain that is characterized by a leg pain in the calf, or thigh, which is caused by inadequate blood flow to the leg muscles and is brought on by leg exercise such as walking.

name: obsolete impotence
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by an abnormal physical or psychological state of a male characterized by inability to copulate because of failure to have, or maintain, an erection.

name: hypoventilation
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by a deficient ventilation of the lungs that results in reduction in the oxygen content or increase in the carbon dioxide content of the blood or both.

name: bradypnea
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by abnormally slow breathing.

name: pleuritic chest pain
definition: A chest pain that is characterized by an inflammation of the pleural cavity with a sharp pain resulting from the exansion of the lungs as the inflammed pleural layers rub against each other.

name: sputum
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by matter discharged from the air passages in diseases of the lungs, bronchi, or upper respiratory tract that contains mucus and often pus, blood, fibrin, or bacterial products.

name: itching
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an uneasy irritating sensation in the upper surface of the skin usually held to result from mild stimulation of pain receptors.

name: anasarca
definition: Anasarca is a edema characterized as generalized edema with accumulation of serum in the connective tissue.

name: urticaria
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by raised red skin wheals (welts) commonly caused by an allergic reaction with wheals that may vary in size from about 5 mm (0.2 inches) in diameter to the size of a dinner plate that are described as severely itchy a stingnig or burning sensation, and having a pale border.

name: paresthesia
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a sensation of pricking, tingling, or creeping on the skin having no objective cause and usually associated with injury or irritation of a sensory nerve or nerve root.

name: abnormal vaginal bleeding
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by bleeding from the uterus that is longer than usual or that occurs at an irregular time. Bleeding may be heavier or lighter than usual and occur often or randomly.

name: toothache
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain in, or about, a tooth or teeth.

name: obsolete heartburn
definition: Heartburn is a pain characterized by a painful burning feeling in your chest or throat that happens when stomach acid backs up into your esophagus.

name: hair loss
definition: A hair symptom that is characterized by the stopping of hair growth (regeneration), which may be a result of hereditary hair loss, immune system overreacts, drugs and treatments, harsh hair-care products, and other factors.

name: elbow pain
definition: A joint pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in or around the elbow.

name: knee pain
definition: A joint pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in or around the knee.

name: shoulder pain
definition: A joint pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in or around the shoulder.

name: obsolete faint
definition: Faint is a alteration of consciousness characterized by a loss of consciousness because of a temporary decrease in the blood supply to the brain.

name: bloody sputum
definition: A sputum that is characterized by blood or bloody mucus discharged from the air passages caused by common forms of infection in the lungs and airways, such as acute bronchitis or pneumonia. Bloody sputum can also come from cancer of the lung.

name: epistaxis
definition: A nose symptom that involves a is loss of blood from the tissue lining the nose.

name: shock
definition: A cardiovascular system symptom that is characterized as a state of profound depression of the vital processes of the body that is characterized by pallor, rapid but weak pulse, rapid and shallow respiration, reduced total blood volume, and low blood pressure and that is caused usually by severe especially crushing injuries, hemorrhage, burns, or major surgery.

name: abnormal weight gain
definition: A weight gain that is characterized as deviating from what is normal or usual, typically in a way that is undesirable or worrying.

name: left upper quadrant abdominal pain
definition: An abdominal pain that is characterized by occurring in the left upper quadrant abdominal pain of the abdomen that can be caused by a stomach ulcer, acute gastritis, a viral infection, or indigestion, or may be an issue with one's lungs.

name: abdominal pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by occurring in the abdomen, i.e. between the chest and groin.

name: nausea
definition: Nausea is a digestive system symptom characterized by an uneasy or unsettled feeling in the stomach together with an urge to vomit.

name: symptom
definition: A symptom is a perceived change in function, sensation, loss, disturbance or appearance reported by a patient indicative of a disease.

name: lack of expected normal physiological development in childhood
failure to thrive
definition: A lack of expected normal physiological development in childhood that is characterized by a decelerated or arrested physical growth (height and weight measurements fall below the third or fifth percentile, or a downward change in growth across two major growth percentiles) and is associated with abnormal growth and development.

name: delayed milestones
definition: A lack of expected normal physiological development in childhood that is characterized by a failure for a child to reach a significant stage at the predicted age and may include walking or talking.

name: early satiety
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by a feeling of being full after a few bites of food, or before you finish a normal-sized meal.

name: obsolete abnormal loss of weight and underweight
underweight
definition: A weight symptom that is characterized by weighing less than the normal amount for one's age, height, and build.

name: abnormality of gait
definition: Abnormality of gait is a nervous system and musculoskeletal system symptom characterized by a difficulty in the manner of walking or moving on foot.

name: persistent vegetative state
definition: An alteration of consciousness that is characterized by an individual with severe brain damage being in a state of partial arousal rather than true awareness. After four weeks in a vegetative state, the patient is classified as being in a persistent vegetative state. After three months in the US and six months in the UK, the diagnosis is classified as a permanent vegetative state after a non-traumatic brain injury, or, one year after a traumatic injury.

name: alteration of consciousness
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by any condition which is significantly different from a normal waking state.

name: dysuria
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the difficult, or painful, discharge of urine.

name: rash
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an eruption on the body typically with little or no elevation above the surface.

name: skin and integumentary tissue symptom
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by the outer layer of the skin starting to replace itself. Often, this happens when skin is damaged, either by disease or injury.

name: urinary incontinence
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the an inability of the body to control the evacuative functions.

name: renal colic
definition: A colic that is characterized by a severe pain produced by the passage of a calculus from the kidney through the ureter.

name: urethral discharge
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by abnormal purulent or mucoid secretions from the penis or, rarely, the female urethra.

name: mixed incontinence (female) (male)
definition: A urinary incontinence that is characterized by urine leakage when you sneeze, cough, laugh, do jarring exercise, or lift something heavy. It is typically a combination of stress and urge incontinence.

name: adult failure to thrive
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by a physical decline in health seen in older adults – typically those with multiple chronic medical conditions – resulting in decreased appetite and poor nutrition, weight loss, inactivity, often accompanied by dehydration, depression, decreasing functional ability, and impaired immune function.

name: headache
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain in the head.

name: throat pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by a painful throat due to inflammation of the fauces and pharynx.

name: aphasia
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by a loss or impairment of the power to use or comprehend words usually resulting from brain damage.

name: pallor
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a deficiency of color especially of the face.

name: flushing
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a markedly red flush in a persons face and often other areas of the skin, from various physiological conditions. Flushing is generally distinguished, despite a close physiological relation between them, from blushing, which is milder, generally restricted to the face or cheeks, and generally assumed to reflect embarrassment. Flushing is also a cardinal symptom of carcinoid syndrome the syndrome that results from hormones (often serotonin or histamine) being secreted into systemic circulation.

name: male stress incontinence
definition: A stress incontinence that is characterized by a compromised external urinary sphincter muscle resulting from surgical or radiotherapeutic manipulation.

name: stridor
definition: An abnormal chest sound that is characterized by a harsh vibrating sound heard during respiration in cases of obstruction of the air passages.

name: hiccough
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a spasmodic inhalation with closure of the glottis accompanied by a peculiar sound.

name: hemoptysis
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an expectoration of blood from some part of the respiratory tract.

name: generalized abdominal pain
definition: An abdominal pain that is characterized by being diffuse or widespread and affecting or involving all of the abdomen.

name: anorexia
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by a loss of appetite especially when prolonged.

name: polyphagia
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by an excessive appetite or eating.

name: transient alteration of awareness
definition: An alteration of consciousness that is characterized by a brief (transient) episode of losing normal awareness or behavior.

name: ascites
definition: An abdominal symptom consisting of an abnormal accumulation of serous fluid in the spaces between tissues and organs in the cavity of the abdomen.

name: tachycardia
definition: Tachycardia is a cardiovascular system symptom consisting of a relatively rapid heart action whether physiological (as after exercise) or pathological.

name: palpitation
definition: Palpitation is a cardiovascykar system symptom characterized by an abnormal awareness of the beating of the heart,whether it is too slow, too fast, irregular, or at its normal frequency when excited by violent exertion, strong emotion, or disease.

name: urge incontinence
definition: A urinary incontinence that is characterized by an involuntary leakage of urine from the bladder when a sudden strong need to urinate is felt, even when the bladder isn't full.

name: post-void dribbling
definition: A urinary incontinence that is characterized by urine remaining in the urethra after voiding the bladder that slowly leaks out after urination.

name: spontaneous ecchymoses
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by the spontaneous escape of blood into the tissues from ruptured blood vessels marked by a livid black-and-blue or purple spot or area.

name: cyanosis
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a bluish or purplish discoloration (as of skin) due to deficient oxygenation of the blood.

name: edema
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an abnormal excess accumulation of serous fluid in connective tissue or in a serous cavity.

name: jaundice
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a yellowish pigmentation of the skin, tissues, and certain body fluids is caused by the deposition of bile pigments that follows interference with normal production and discharge of bile (as in certain liver diseases) or excessive breakdown of red blood cells (as after internal hemorrhage or in various hemolytic states).

name: painful respiration
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a feeling of discomfort when breathing in or out.  The pain may be the result of infection, musculoskeletal injury, and heart problems.

name: epigastric abdominal pain
definition: An abdominal pain that is characterized by occurring in the epigastrium, i.e. the upper part of the abdomen below the rib cage.

name: memory loss
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by an unusual forgetfulness. One may not be able to remember new events, recall one or more memories of the past, or both.  Memory loss may be for a short time and then resolve (transient), or it may not go away and get worse over time.

name: transient paralysis of limb
definition: A paralysis that is characterized by a loss of some, or all, muscle control in a limb, and which lasts for only a short time (i.e. is temporary).

name: disturbances of sensation of smell and taste
meningismus
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by a state of meningeal irritation with symptoms suggesting meningitis that often occurs at the onset of acute febrile diseases especially in children.

name: urinary retention
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by an inability to empty the bladder completely during the process of voiding (urination).

name: incomplete bladder emptying
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by a bladder that is not empty.

name: polydipsia
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by an excessive or abnormal thirst.

name: urinary frequency
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the need to urinate many times during the day, at night, or both but in normal or less-than-normal volumes.  Frequency may be accompanied by a sensation of an urgent need to void (urgency of urination).

name: nocturia
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by urination at night especially when excessive.

name: polyuria
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the excessive secretion of urine.

name: short stature
definition: A lack of expected normal physiological development in childhood that is characterized by an individual's height being in the 3rd percentile for the mean height of a given age, sex, and population group.

name: oliguria
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the reduced excretion of urine.

name: diarrhea
definition: Diarrhea is a feces and droppng symptom involving the abnormally frequent intestinal evacuations with more or less fluid stools.

name: insomnia
definition: Insomnia is a sleep disturbance characterized by prolonged and usually abnormal inability to obtain adequate sleep.

name: splitting of urinary stream
definition: A urinary stream symptom that is characterized by a split in the urine flow resulting in it streaming in two directions.

name: sleep apnea
definition: An apnea that is characterized by brief periods of recurrent cessation of breathing during sleep that is caused especially by obstruction of the airway or a disturbance in the brain's respiratory center and is associated especially with excessive daytime sleepiness.

name: hypersomnia
definition: Hypersomnia is a sleep disturbance characterized by sleeping for excessive periods at intervals with intervening periods of normal duration of sleeping and waking.

name: overflow incontinence
definition: A urinary incontinence that is characterized by a bladder that does not empty completely, resulting in a bladder that is too full, which leads to overflow and unexpected leaking.

name: abnormal chest sound
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a sound of breathing that is not similar to that of the sound of moving air and may include: rhonchi (a low-pitched breath sound), crackles (a high-pitched breath sound), wheezing (a high-pitched whistling sound caused by narrowing of the bronchial tubes), and stridor (a harsh, vibratory sound caused by narrowing of the upper airway).

name: extravasation of urine
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by an injury of the urethra in its bulbous or membranous portion, which leads to a collection of urine in other cavities, such as the perineal space, the scrotum, the penis and the connective tissue of the anterior abdominal wall.

name: slowing of urinary stream
definition: A urinary stream symptom that is characterized by a slow or weak stream of urine.

name: urinary urgency
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by a strong and immediate need to urinate due to an increase in pressure in the bladder, resulting in difficulty to hold in the urine. This can occur regardless of whether the bladder is full.

name: abnormal involuntary movement
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by an inability to control bodily movement and may be a symptom of cerebrovascular diseases, dyskinesia, tremor, chorea, dystonia and myoclonus.

name: febrile convulsion
definition: A convulsion that is characterized by occurring in young children between six months and five years of age and which is triggered by fever.

name: convulsion
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by an abnormal violent and involuntary contraction or series of contractions of the muscles.

name: respiratory abnormality
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a respiration that is not normal and may include, but is not limited to: apnea, eupnea, orthopnea, dyspnea hyperpnea, hyperventilation, hypoventilation, tachypnea, Kussmaul respiration, Cheyne-Stokes respiration, sighing respiration, Biot respiration, apneustic breathing, central neurogenic hyperventilation, and central neurogenic hypoventilation.

name: cheyne-stokes respiration
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by a specific form of periodic breathing (waxing and waning amplitude of flow or tidal volume) characterized by a crescendo-decrescendo pattern of respiration between central apneas or central hypopneas.

name: apnea
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by transient cessation of respiration whether normal (as in hibernating animals) or abnormal (as that caused by certain drugs).

name: hyperventilation
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by excessive ventilation characterized by excessive rate and depth of respiration leading to abnormal loss of carbon dioxide from the blood.

name: orthopnea
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by a difficulty in breathing that occurs when lying down and is relieved upon changing to an upright position (as in congestive heart failure).

name: tachypnea
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by an increased rate of respiration and shallow breathing.

name: wheezing
definition: An abnormal chest sound that is characterized by breathing with difficulty usually with a whistling sound.

name: coma
definition: An alteration of consciousness that is characterized by a deep state of prolonged unconsciousness in which a person cannot be awakened, fails to respond normally to painful stimuli, light, or sound, lacks a normal wake-sleep cycle and does not initiate voluntary actions.

name: nocturnal enuresis
definition: A urinary incontinence that is characterized by involuntary urination at night in children five years of age or older.

name: hallucination
definition: Hallucination is a general symptom where there is a perception of something (as a visual image or a sound) with no external cause usually arising from a disorder of the nervous system (as in delirium tremens or in functional psychosis without known neurological disease) or in response to drugs (as LSD).

name: syncope and collapse
definition: An alteration of consciousness that is characterized by a loss of consciousness resulting from insufficient blood flow to the brain and limb weakness progressing to collapse.

name: generalized hyperhidrosis
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by excessive sweating, i.e. the production of more sweat than is required to regulate body temperature.  Generalized hyperhidrosis is caused by non-thermoregulatory stimuli and affects the entire body.

name: dizziness
definition: A  balance symptom that is characterized by a sensation of unsteadiness accompanied by a feeling of movement within the head.

name: fever
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a rise of body temperature above the normal, whether as a natural response (as to infection) or artificially induced for therapeutic reasons.

name: cough
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an explosive expulsion of air from the lungs acting as a protective mechanism to clear the air passages or as a symptom of pulmonary disturbance.

name: left lower quadrant abdominal pain
definition: An abdominal pain that is characterized by occurring in the left lower quadrant of the abdomen that is often related to the digestive tract, but can also be related to conditions of the body wall, skin, blood vessels, urinary tract, or reproductive organs.

name: alexia
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by a loss of ability to read.

name: acute renal failure
definition: A renal failure that is characterized by a severe and sudden onset of renal failure.

name: conscious disturbance
definition: An alteration of consciousness that is characterized by a disturbance in sentience (the ability to experience feelings and sensations) or awareness of one's internal and external existence, i.e. inhibited or absent self-awareness.

name: exanthema
definition: A rash characterized by a widespread skin eruption usually occurring in children that is a symptom of a more general disease.

name: hip pain
definition: A joint pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in or around the hip.

name: maculopapular rash
definition: A rash characterized by papule(s), which are a raised area of the skin and macule(s), which are a flat red area of the skin.

name: papular rash
definition: A rash characterized by papule(s), which are a raised area of the skin.

name: ankle rash
definition: A rash characterized by an inflammatory reaction of the skin on the ankles.

name: respiratory failure
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a difficulty to breathe on one's own and develops when the lungs cannot get enough oxygen into the blood.

name: synovitis
definition: Synovitis is a joint inflammation characterized by an inflammation of a synovial membrane usually with pain and swelling of the joint.

name: tache noire
definition: A skin ulcer that is characterized by a a small dark-centered ulcer that appears at the site of a tick bite and is the primary lesion of boutonneuse fever.

name: irritability
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by a quick excitability to annoyance, impatience, or anger.

name: pareses
definition: A paralysis that is charachterized by a slight or partial paralysis.

name: purpuric rash
definition: A rash characterized by a red or purple hued small spots of blood appear on the skin caused by conditions that result in blood leaking into the skin and other body surfaces that does not fade when pressed upon.

name: shakes
definition: Shakes is a general symptom characterized by a condition of trembling.

name: abnormal behavior
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by behavior that is atypical or statistically uncommon within a particular culture, or that is maladaptive, or detrimental to an individual, or those around that individual.

name: bradykinesia
definition: Bradykinesia is a hypokinesia characterized by an extreme slowness in the execution of movements and reflexes.

name: acute diarrhea
definition: Acute diarrhea is a diarrhea with either or both a rapid onset or a short course.

name: acute enteritis
definition: Acute enteritis is a enteritis with either or both a rapid onset and a short course which is usually due to bacteria or virus.

name: acute mental dysfunction
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by a severe and sudden onset of disturbance in the normal operation of one's cognition, emotional regulation, or behaviour.

name: acute dyspnea
definition: A dyspnea that is characterized by a severe and sudden onset.

name: acute weight loss
definition: A weight loss that is characterized by a severe and sudden onset.

name: aggressive behavior
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by behavior aimed at harming a person, or animal, or damaging physical property.

name: altered mental status
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by a host of presentations that include changes in cognition, mood, behavior, and/or level of arousal.

name: obsolete tachypnoea
definition: Tachypnoea is a respiratory system and chest symptom characterized by an increased rate of respiration.

name: chronic cough
definition: A cough that is characterized by an explosive expulsion of air from the lungs acting as a protective mechanism to clear the air passages or as a symptom of pulmonary disturbance marked by long duration, by frequent recurrence over a long time, and often by slowly progressing seriousness.

name: obsolete chronic fatigue syndrome
definition: Chronic fatigue syndrome is a fatigue characterized by a disorder of uncertain cause that is characterized by persistent profound fatigue usually accompanied by impairment in short-term memory or concentration, sore throat, tender lymph nodes, muscle or joint pain, and headache unrelated to any preexisting medical condition and that typically has an onset at about 30 years of age.

name: circling movement
definition: An abnormal involuntary movement that is characterized by an inability to walk in a straight line.

name: decreased milk production
definition: A nutrition, metabolism, and development symptom that is characterized by a decrease in the production of milk in breastfeeding mothers.

name: decreased sucking
definition: A feeding difficulties and mismanagement that is characterized by a decrease in muscle coordination to form a suck response so that the child can ingest milk.

name: distended loops of intestines on rectal
expressive aphasia
definition: An aphasia that is characterized by damage to, or a developmental issues in, the anterior regions of the brain, including (but not limited to) the left inferior frontal region known as Broca's area. Sufferers of this form of aphasia exhibit the common problem of agrammatism. For them, speech is difficult to initiate, non-fluent, labored, and halting.

name: infertility
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized the biological inability of a man or a woman to contribute to conception; or, the state of a woman who is unable to carry a pregnancy to full term.

name: skin desquamation
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by the peeling off of skin in the form of scales.

name: loss of consciousness
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a state in which an individual lacks normal awareness of self and the surrounding environment and one's ability to remain awake, aware, and oriented is impaired.

name: memory impairment
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a diminished or reduced ability to remember things such as dates and names, and increased forgetfulness.

name: pulmonary consolidation
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a region of normally compressible lung tissue that has filled with liquid instead of air.

name: rapid respiration
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by an increased breathing rate, with more than 20 breaths per minute in an adult, while in children, the number of breaths per minute can be a higher resting rate than seen in adults.

name: renal failure
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by a loss of excretory function in one or both kidneys, leading to retention of nitrogenous waste products from the blood.

name: obsolete stroke
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by a sudden diminution or loss of consciousness, sensation, and voluntary motion caused by rupture or obstruction (as by a clot) of a blood vessel of the brain.

name: obsolete suppurative pneumonia
definition: A pneumonia that is characterized by the formation of pus and destruction of pulmonary tissue; abscess formation may occur.

name: respiratory tract mucosa ulcer
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an ulceration (dying and sloughing) of the bronchial or bronchiolar epithelium, exposing the underlying basement membrane.

name: bronchopulmonary bleeding
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by bleeding (hemorrhage) in either or both the bronchi and the lungs.

name: gum bleeding
definition: Gum bleeding is a mouth symptom characterized by a copious discharge of blood from the blood vessels of the mucosal tissue that lies over the alveolar bone.

name: enanthem
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by an eruption on a mucous surface.

name: facial edema
definition: An adema that is characterized by an abnormal excess accumulation of serous fluid in connective tissue of the face.

name: menorrhagia
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized an abnormally profuse menstrual flow.

name: parotid pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, in the parotid gland, which is a salivary gland located in front of the ears. (Additional salivary glands include the submandibular and sublingual glands.) Pain is attributed to swelling of the gland.

name: petechiae
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a minute reddish or purplish spot containing blood that appears in skin or mucous membrane as a result of localized hemorrhage.

name: retrobulbar pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain situated, or occurring, behind the eyeball.

name: testicular pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain in, or about, a testis (testicle) or testes. Testicular pain can be caused by nerve damage, sexually transmitted infections, gangrene, swelling, hernia, kidney stones, inflammation, enlarged veins, fluid in the testicle, or a severe condition known as testicular torsion.

name: dysfunctions associated with arousal from sleep
chronic enteritis
definition: Chronic enteritis is a enteritis with slow progress, long duration, or frequent recurrence which can be due to Crohn's disease, giardiasis, tuberculosis, coeliac disease, or rarely due to Whipple's disease.

name: sinus bradycardia
definition: Sinus bradycardia is a bradycardia where the sinus rhythm is abnormally slow bradycardia consisting of a sinus rhythm at a rate lower than 60 beats per minute.

name: junctional tachycardia
definition: Junctional tachycardia is a tachycardia associated with the generation of impulses in a locus in the region of the atrioventricular node.

name: paroxysmal tachycardia
definition: Paroxysmal tachycardia is a tachycardia that begins and ends abruptly and that is initiated by a premature supraventricular beat originating in the atrium or in the atrioventricular node or bundle of His or by a premature ventricular beat.

name: sinus tachycardia
definition: Sinus tachycardia is a tachychardia characterized by an abnormally rapid sinus rhythm specifically a sinus rhythm at a rate greater than 100 beats per minute.

name: ventricular tachycardia
definition: A tachycardia that is associated with the generation of improper electrical impulses within the ventricles, characterized by an electrocardiogram showing a rate of greater than 120 BPM and three or more wide QRS complexes in a row.

name: sore eyes
definition: Sore eyes is a eye symptom characterized by an inflammation of the thin covering of the eyeball and the inner eyelid brought about by a viral infection which may be highly contagious.

name: neck pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by an unpleasant sensation localized in the neck that usually indicates the body is threatened or damaged. The sensation may be sharp or dull, short-lived or chronic, intermittent or continual.

name: phantom pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by a painful sensation that is perceived to originate in the amputated portion of the extremety. Patients may have localized pain that originates in the stump.

name: nociceptive pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by originating from other than the peripheral and central nervous systems, and which is caused by activation of nociceptive fibers.

name: neuropathic pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by being experienced by cancer patients and which is caused by radiotherapy or chemotherapy damage to nerves, when cancer invades or compresses nerves, or when, during cancer treatment. This type of pain is typically described as burning, electrical, or strange feeling.

name: visceral pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by originating from organ tissues of the thorax, abdomen, or pelvis.  It characterizes as deep, vague, and difficult to locate pain, that radiates away from the affected organ.

name: hypoesthesia
definition: A sensation perception that is characterized by a reduced sense of touch or sensation, or a partial loss of sensitivity to sensory stimuli.

name: hypoalgesia
definition: A sensation perception that is characterized by a diminished sensitivity to painful stimulation.

name: hyperalgesia
definition: A sensation perception that is characterized by an increased response to a painful stimulus.

name: chronic pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by ranging from mild to severe and which continues beyond the expected healing phase.

name: breakthrough pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by occurring with movement and is not controlled by a scheduled pain medication regimen, such that the pain breaks through the current regimen. This is usually referred to in the context of a short and long acting opioid, the short acting opioid being used to treat the breakthrough pain.

name: acute pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by being severe but lasting a relatively short time.

name: allodynia
definition: A pain that is characterized by a painful sensation with a normal, non-painful stimulation.

name: reactive hyperemia
definition: Reactive hyperemia is a hyperemia occurring due to the dilation of arteriolar smooth muscle to increase blood flow in response to a profound increase in blood flow to an organ after being occluded. There will be a shortage of oxygen and a build-up of metabolic waste.

name: active hyperemia
definition: Active hyperemia is a hyperemia occurring due to the dilation of arteriolar smooth muscle to increase blood flow in response to an increase in metabolism.

name: functional hyperemia
definition: Functional hyperemia is a hyperemia occurring due to an increase in blood flow to a tissue due to the presence of metabolites and a change in general conditions.

name: face hyperemia
definition: Hyperemia of the face is a head symptom consisting of an excess of blood in the tissues of the face as from an increased flow of blood due to vasodilation.

name: hyperemia of the neck
definition: Hyperemia of the neck is a neck symptom consisting of an excess of blood in the tissues of the neck as from an increased flow of blood due to vasodilation.

name: chest hyperemia
definition: Hyperemia of the chest is a cardiovascular system symptom consisting of an excess of blood in the tissues of the chest as from an increased flow of blood due to vasodilation.

name: spastic paralysis
definition: A paralysis that is characterized by a tonic spasm of the affected muscles and with increased tendon reflexes.

name: motor paralysis
definition: A paralysis that is characterized by a complete or partial loss of function the voluntary muscles.

name: stillbirth
definition: A reproductive system symptom that is characterized by the birth of a dead fetus; in which  a fetus that has died in the uterus, or during labor, or delivery, exits a woman's body.

name: congested sclera
definition: Congested sclera is a hyperemia characterized as the congestion of the vessels of the outer layer of the eye containing collagen and elastic fibers.

name: gross hematuria
definition: A hematuria that is characterized by the production of a visible redness in the urine.

name: anuria
definition: A urinary system symptom that is characterized by the absence of, or by defective, urine excretion.

name: stress incontinence
definition: A urinary incontinence that is characterized by an involuntary leakage of urine from the bladder accompanying physical activity (as in laughing, coughing, sneezing, or physical exercise) which places increased pressure on the abdomen.

name: hypermenorrhea
definition: A menorrhagia that is characterized by an abnormally profuse or prolonged menstrual flow.

name: metrorrhagia
definition: A menorrhagia that is characterized by an irregular uterine bleeding, especially between menstrual periods.

name: subjective vertigo
definition: A vertigo that is characterized by a sensation that one's body is revolving in space.

name: objective vertigo
definition: A vertigo that is characterized by a sensation that the external world is revolving.

name: hypokinesia
definition: Hypokinesia is a musculoskeletal system  symptom characterized by the slow or diminished movement of body musculature. It may be associated with basal ganglia diseases; mental disorders; prolonged inactivity due to illness; experimental protocols used to evaluate the physiologic effects of immobility; and other conditions.

name: rigidity hypokinesia
definition: Rigidity hypokinesia a type of hypokinesia described as the increase in muscle tension when moved by an outside force.

name: postural instability hypokinesia
definition: Postural instability hypokinesia is a hypokinesia described as a loss of ability to maintain an upright posture.

name: freezing hypokinesia
definition: Freezing hypokinesia is a hypkinesia where a person can not move their muscles how they want them to.

name: referred pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by pain which is subjectively localized in one region although it is due to irritation in another region.

name: facial tremor
definition: Facial tremor is a head symptom characterized by a trembling or shaking of the muscles of the face usually from physical weakness, emotional stress, or disease, may be emphasized by the firm closure of the eyes, elevation of the eyebrows, or drawing down and outward of the corners of the mouth.

name: cervical edema
definition: Cervical edema is a neck symptom characterized by an abnormal excess accumulation of serous fluid in the soft tissue of the cervical area.

name: gastrointestinal bleeding
definition: A digestive system symptom characterized by bleeding from one or more of the areas of the digestive or gastrointestinal (GI) tract that includes the espophagus, stomach, small intestine, large intestine or colon, rectum and anus.

name: breathing problems
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by a shortness of breath, a hard or uncomfortable intake of air, or the feeling that you're not getting enough air.

name: nasal congestion
definition: A congestion that is characterized by a blockage of the nasal passages, usually due to the membranes lining the nose becoming swollen from inflamed blood vessels.

name: icteric eyes
definition: Icteric eyes is a eye symptom characterized by yellowed eyes due to bile or bilirubin accumulation.

name: icteric mucous membrane
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by yellowed mucous membranes due to bile or bilirubin accumulation.

name: icteric skin
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by yellowed skin due to bile or bilirubin accumulation.

name: otitis
definition: Otitis is a ear symptom characterized as a general term for inflammation or infection of the ear, in both humans and other animals.

name: hematoma
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a mass of usually clotted blood that forms in a tissue, organ, or body space as a result of a broken blood vessel generally the result of hemorrhage, or more specifically, internal bleeding.

name: lameness
definition: Lameness is a musculoskeletal system symptom where a person is physically disabled as the result of having a body part and especially a limb so disabled as to impair freedom of movement.

name: pericardial effusion
definition: Pericardial effusion is a cardiovascular system symptom where there is an abnormal accumulation of fluid in the pericardial cavity.

name: transient fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by a rise of body temperature above the normal that is sustained for only a short period of time.

name: low-grade fever
definition: A mild fever that is characterized by a fever that does not exceed 38.5 degrees Celsius (101.3 degrees Fahrenheit).

name: prolonged fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by as  persisting over a prolonged period of time.

name: mild fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by being mild in form.

name: high fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by an elevated temperature.

name: very high fever
definition: A high fever that is characterized by extremely high temperatures.

name: hyperpyrexia
definition: A fever that is characterized by an extreme elevation of body temperature greater than, or equal to, 41.5 degrees Celsius (106.7 degrees Fahrenheit).

name: Pel-Epstein fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by association with Hodgkin's lymphoma, where the fever alternates weekly from high to low.

name: continuous fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by a temperature remaining above normal throughout the day and which does not fluctuate more than 1 degree Celsius in 24 hours.

name: remittent fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by a fever where the temperature remains above normal throughout the day and fluctuates more than 1 degree Celsius in 24 hours.

name: relapsing fever
definition: A fever that is characterized by  body temperature periodically rising and falling.

name: sensation perception
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by interpretation of the information perceived by sensory receptors.

name: hypotensive
definition: A low blood pressure characterized by or due to abnormally low blood pressure, especially in the arteries of the systemic circulation.

name: cold clammy skin
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by cold, moist and sticky skin.

name: anaphylactic shock
definition: An acute allergic reaction to an antigen to which the body has become hypersensitive.

name: exophthalmos
definition: An abnormal protrusion or displacement of an eye or other body part.

name: ventricular bradycardia
definition: A bradycardia associated with the generation of impules in the ventricles when impules from the atria fail to reach them, characterized by an electrocardiogram showing a heart rate below 50 BPM and a broad QRS complex.

name: cardiac fibrillation
definition: An arrhythmia characterized by rapid, irregular, and unsynchronized contraction of muscle fibers within the heart.

name: ventricular fibrillation
definition: A cardiac fibrillation associated with quivering of the lower chambers of the heart, preventing blood from being pumped and causing cardiac arrest.

name: allergic reaction
definition: An immune system symptom that is characterized by sensitivities to substances called allergens.

name: vomiting
definition: Vomiting is a digestive system symptom characterized by throwing up the stomach contents.

name: hematemesis
definition: A vomiting where there is vomiting of blood.

name: pulmonary edema
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by an abnormal accumulation of fluid in the lungs.

name: diaphoresis
definition: A sweat that is characterized by excessive sweating commonly associated with shock and other medical emergency conditions.

name: dyspnea
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by difficult or labored respiration.

name: hemorrhagic mediastinitis
definition: A respiratory abnormality that is characterized by inflammation of the mediastinum (the chest cavity, which contains the heart, the thymus gland, some lymph nodes, and parts of the esophagus, aorta, thyroid, and parathyroid glands) as the result of bleeding.

name: eschar
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a scab formed especially after a burn.

name: boil
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a localized swelling and inflammation of the skin resulting from usually bacterial infection of a hair follicle and adjacent tissue, having a hard central core, and forming pus.

name: muscle pain
definition: A pain that is characterized by a pain in one or more muscles.

name: pustule
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by a small circumscribed elevation of the skin containing pus and having an inflamed base.

name: obsolete pneumonia
definition: A pneumonitis that is characterized by an inflammatory illness of the lung resulting from a variety of causes including infection with bacteria, viruses, fungi, or parasites, and chemical or physical injury to the lungs. Its cause may also be officially described as idiopathic, that is, unknown, when infectious causes have been excluded.

name: arthritis
definition: Arthritis is a musculoskeletal system symptom characterized as an inflammation of joints due to infectious, metabolic, or constitutional causes.

name: spondylitis
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of the vertebrae.

name: meningitis
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by an inflammation of the meninges and especially of the pia mater and the arachnoid.

name: sweaty
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by the excretion of moisture in visible quantities through the opening of the sweat glands.

name: malaise
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by an indefinite feeling of debility or lack of health, often indicative of or accompanying the onset of an illness.

name: fatigue
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a weariness or exhaustion from labor, exertion, or stress.

name: necrotic lesion
definition: A skin and integumentary tissue symptom that is characterized by regions of cell death to living tissue in an organ, which has suffered damage through injury or disease, such as a wound, ulcer, abscess, or tumor.

name: lightheadedness
definition: A  balance symptom that is characterized by a condition of being dizzy or on the verge of fainting, particularly when one arises to a standing position. Lightheadedness is a predictable consequence of any medication tending to lower blood pressure.

name: constipation
definition: Constipation is a feces and droppings symptom involving the abnormally delayed or infrequent passage of dry hardened feces. Constipation may be categorized into three subtypes: normal-transit, slow-transit, and pelvic floor dysfunction.

name: behavioral symptom
definition: A nervous system symptom that is characterized by an involvement, or relation to, or emphasizes behavior.

name: hyperactivity
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by an increase in movement, impulsive actions, a shorter attention span, and being easily distracted.

name: limited attention
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by a restricted rate of information processing by the brain.

name: communication difficulty
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by speech, language and communication needs or communication disabilities.

name: obsessive interests
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by obsessive and highly-focused interests.

name: repetitive behavior
definition: A behavioral symptom that is characterized by an unusual repetitive motor movements or manipulation of objects.

name: intracranial hemorrhage
definition: A hemorrhage that is characterized by any bleeding occurring within the skull.

name: intracerebral hemorrhage
definition: A hemorrhage that is characterized by bleeding within the brain tissue itself.

name: subdural hemorrhage
definition: A hemorrhage that is characterized by bleeding that occurs within the skull of head but outside the actual brain tissue.

name: airway stenosis
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by a narrowing in the airway that obstructs the passage of air into the lungs.  Examples include tracheal and laryngotracheal stenosis.

name: apthous ulcer
definition: A skin ulcer that is characterized by a small recurrent, painful, round or ovoid ulcers with well-defined erythematous margins, like a halo, and a central yellow or gray floor found in the soft tissue of the oral cavity.

name: ageusia
definition: A disturbances of sensation of smell and taste that is characterized by a complete loss of taste function of the tongue.

name: agitation
definition: A neurological and physiological symptom that is characterized by a feeling of irritability or severe restlessness.

name: barking croup cough
definition: A cough that is characterized by a tight, low-pitched, and barky (like a barking seal) cough.

name: abnormal weight loss
definition: A weight loss that is characterized as deviating from what is normal or usual, typically in a way that is undesirable or worrying.

name: chronic weight loss
definition: A weight loss that is characterized by conditions that last 1 year or more and require ongoing medical attention, or limit activities of daily living, or both.

name: acute weight gain
definition: A weight gain that is characterized by a severe and sudden onset.

name: chronic weight gain
definition: A weight gain that is characterized by conditions that last 1 year or more and require ongoing medical attention, or limit activities of daily living, or both.

name: overweight
definition: A weight symptom that is characterized by being too heavy for one’s height. Excess body weight can come from fat, muscle, bone, and/or water retention. Being overweight does not always mean being obese.

name: postnasal drainage
definition: A nose symptom that is characterized by an an excessive secretion of mucous down the back of the throat.

name: bone conduction hyperacusis
definition: An ear symptom - need proper definition - placeholder for xref.

name: bronchospasm
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by constriction of the air passages of the lung (as in asthma) by spasmodic contraction of the bronchial muscles.

name: caseation
definition: A respiratory system and chest symptom that is characterized by necrosis of tissue with conversion of damaged tissue into a soft cheesy substance.

name: wet cough
